## Example 5 — Power Property of Logarithms

Use `log2 6 ≈ 2.585` to approximate `log2 1296`.

Because:

`1296 = 6^4`

Then:

`log2 1296 = log2(6^4)`

`= 4 log2 6`

`≈ 4(2.585)`

`≈ 10.34`

### Check

Use `log2 3 ≈ 1.5850` to approximate `log2 243`.

